## 3. High-Voltage Electrical Isolation Boundaries

To ensure safe operation of the Electro-Hydrodynamic (EHD) ionization array, explicit physical clearance zones must be maintained around all conductive surfaces.

* **Ceramic Track Clearance:** The Alumina ($Al_2O_3$) isolation tracks must project a minimum of $15\text{ mm}$ past the ends of the tungsten emitter wires to eliminate surface tracking arcs to the metal frame.
* **HV Air Gap Boundary:** Maintain a strict $50\text{ mm}$ absolute air gap (or a minimum of $12\text{ mm}$ solid Delrin/PTFE insulation barrier) between the high-voltage distribution node and the low-voltage MHD collection busbars or aluminum chassis panels.
* **Flush Electrode Depth:** Copper collection plates must be seated into the 3D-printed channel floors matching a tolerance profile of $+0.05\text{ mm} / -0.00\text{ mm}$. No part of the electrode may protrude above the channel surface, preventing localized hydrodynamic cavitation.

---

## 4. Mechanical Fastener & Interface Specs

* **Manifold Couplings:** High-flow, flat-face, dry-break quick disconnect couplings on all branch lines to enable fluid-free isolation of active cores.
* **Gaskets:** Dual-groove Viton O-Rings (Dash size -222, 75 Shore A Durometer) rated for continuous thermal cycling from $-10^\circ\text{C}$ to $+150^\circ\text{C}$ across zeotropic fluid boundaries.
* **Chassis Fasteners:** M6 Grade 8.8 hex bolts with nylon-locking nuts, torqued to a maximum specification of $9.5\text{ N}\cdot\text{m}$.
